  27 class PointerDefaultCtor : public FunctionSymbol
  28 {
  29 public:
  30     PointerDefaultCtor(TypeSymbol* type_, const Span& span);
  31     SymbolAccess DeclaredAccess() const override { return SymbolAccess::public_; }
  32     void GenerateCall(Emitter& emitter, std::vector<GenObject*>& genObjects, OperationFlags flags, const Span& span) override;
  33     bool IsBasicTypeOperation() const override { return true; }
  34     const char* ClassName() const override { return "PointerDefaultCtor"; }
  35 private:
  36     TypeSymbol* type;
  37     llvm::Value* nullValue;
  38 };
  39 
  40 PointerDefaultCtor::PointerDefaultCtor(TypeSymbol* type_, const Span& span) : FunctionSymbol(span, U"@constructor"), type(type_), nullValue(nullptr)
  41 {
  42     SetGroupName(U"@constructor");
  43     SetAccess(SymbolAccess::public_);
  44     ParameterSymbol* thisParam = new ParameterSymbol(span, U"this");
  45     thisParam->SetType(type->AddPointer(span));
  46     AddMember(thisParam);
  47     ComputeName();
  48 }
  49 
  50 void PointerDefaultCtor::GenerateCall(Emitter& emitter, std::vector<GenObject*>& genObjects, OperationFlags flags, const Span& span)
  51 {
  52     Assert(genObjects.size() == 1, "default constructor needs one object");
  53     if (!nullValue)
  54     {
  55         nullValue = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(type->IrType(emitter));
  56     }
  57     emitter.Stack().Push(nullValue);
  58     genObjects[0]->Store(emitter, OperationFlags::none);
  59 }

  61 class PointerDefaultConstructorOperation : public Operation
  62 {
  63 public:
  64     PointerDefaultConstructorOperation(BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit_);
  65     void CollectViableFunctions(ContainerScope* containerScope, const std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>& arguments, BoundFunction* currentFunction, 
  66         std::unordered_set<FunctionSymbol*>& viableFunctions, std::unique_ptr<Exception>& exception, const Span& span) override;
  67 private:
  68     std::unordered_map<TypeSymbol*, FunctionSymbol*> functionMap;
  69     std::vector<std::unique_ptr<FunctionSymbol>> functions;
  70 };
  71 
  72 PointerDefaultConstructorOperation::PointerDefaultConstructorOperation(BoundCompileUnit& boundCompileUnit_) : Operation(U"@constructor", 1, boundCompileUnit_)
  73 {
  74 }
  75 
  76 void PointerDefaultConstructorOperation::CollectViableFunctions(ContainerScope* containerScope, const std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>& arguments, BoundFunction* currentFunction, 
  77     std::unordered_set<FunctionSymbol*>& viableFunctions, std::unique_ptr<Exception>& exception, const Span& span)
  78 {
  79     TypeSymbol* type = arguments[0]->GetType();
  80     if (type->PointerCount() <= 1) return;
  81     if (type->IsReferenceType()) return;
  82     TypeSymbol* pointerType = type->RemovePointer(span);
  83     FunctionSymbol* function = functionMap[pointerType];
  84     if (!function)
  85     {
  86         function = new PointerDefaultCtor(pointerType, span);
  87         function->SetSymbolTable(GetSymbolTable());
  88         function->SetParent(&GetSymbolTable()->GlobalNs());
  89         functionMap[pointerType] = function;
  90         functions.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<FunctionSymbol>(function));
  91     }
  92     viableFunctions.insert(function);
  93 }

 108 {
 109     SetGroupName(U"@constructor");
 110     SetAccess(SymbolAccess::public_);

 119 
 120 void PointerCopyCtor::GenerateCall(Emitter& emitter, std::vector<GenObject*>& genObjects, OperationFlags flags, const Span& span)
 121 {
 122     Assert(genObjects.size() == 2, "copy constructor needs two objects");
 123     genObjects[1]->Load(emitter, OperationFlags::none);
 124     if ((flags & OperationFlags::leaveFirstArg) != OperationFlags::none)
 125     {
 126         emitter.Stack().Dup();
 127         llvm::Value* ptr = emitter.Stack().Pop();
 128         emitter.SaveObjectPointer(ptr);
 129     }
 130     genObjects[0]->Store(emitter, OperationFlags::none);
 131 }

 195 void PointerMoveCtor::GenerateCall(Emitter& emitter, std::vector<GenObject*>& genObjects, OperationFlags flags, const Span& span)
 196 {
 197     Assert(genObjects.size() == 2, "move constructor needs two objects");
 198     genObjects[1]->Load(emitter, OperationFlags::none);
 199     llvm::Value* rvalueRefValue = emitter.Stack().Pop();
 200     emitter.Stack().Push(emitter.Builder().CreateLoad(rvalueRefValue));
 201     if ((flags & OperationFlags::leaveFirstArg) != OperationFlags::none)
 202     {
 203         emitter.Stack().Dup();
 204         llvm::Value* ptr = emitter.Stack().Pop();
 205         emitter.SaveObjectPointer(ptr);
 206     }
 207     genObjects[0]->Store(emitter, OperationFlags::none);
 208 }

 439 void PointerReturnOperation::CollectViableFunctions(ContainerScope* containerScope, const std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>& arguments, BoundFunction* currentFunction, 
 440     std::unordered_set<FunctionSymbol*>& viableFunctions, std::unique_ptr<Exception>& exception, const Span& span)
 441 {
 442     TypeSymbol* type = arguments[0]->GetType();

 446     if (!function)
 447     {
 448         function = new PointerReturn(type, span);

1914 void ClassDefaultConstructorOperation::CollectViableFunctions(ContainerScope* containerScope, const std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>>& arguments, BoundFunction* currentFunction, 
1915     std::unordered_set<FunctionSymbol*>& viableFunctions, std::unique_ptr<Exception>& exception, const Span& span)
1916 {
1917     TypeSymbol* type = arguments[0]->GetType();
1918     if (type->PointerCount() != 1 || !type->RemovePointer(span)->PlainType(span)->IsClassTypeSymbol()) return;
1919     ClassTypeSymbol* classType = static_cast<ClassTypeSymbol*>(type->BaseType());
1920     if (classType->IsStatic())
1921     {
1922         exception.reset(new Exception(GetModule(), "cannot create an instance of a static class", span, classType->GetSpan()));
1923         return;
1924     }
1925     if (classType->DefaultConstructor())
1926     {
1927         viableFunctions.insert(classType->DefaultConstructor());
1928         return;
1929     }
1930     GetBoundCompileUnit().FinalizeBinding(classType);
1931     FunctionSymbol* function = functionMap[classType];
1932     if (!function)
1933     {
1934         std::unique_ptr<ClassDefaultConstructor> defaultConstructor(new ClassDefaultConstructor(classType, span));
1935         ConstructorSymbol* prevDefaultConstructor = classType->DefaultConstructor();
1936         classType->SetDefaultConstructor(defaultConstructor.get());
1937         defaultConstructor->SetCompileUnit(GetBoundCompileUnit().GetCompileUnitNode());
1938         defaultConstructor->SetSymbolTable(&GetBoundCompileUnit().GetSymbolTable());
1939         if (GenerateImplementation(defaultConstructor.get(), containerScope, currentFunction, exception, span))
1940         {
1941             function = defaultConstructor.get();
1942             function->SetSymbolTable(GetSymbolTable());
1943             function->SetParent(classType);
1944             function->SetLinkOnceOdrLinkage();
1945             function->SetInline();
1946             functionMap[classType] = function;
1947             classType->AddMember(defaultConstructor.release());
1948         }
1949         else
1950         {
1951             classType->SetDefaultConstructor(prevDefaultConstructor);
1952             return;
1953         }
1954     }
1955     viableFunctions.insert(function);
1956 }
1957 
1958 bool ClassDefaultConstructorOperation::GenerateImplementation(ClassDefaultConstructor* defaultConstructor, ContainerScope* containerScope, BoundFunction* currentFunction, 
1959     std::unique_ptr<Exception>& exception, const Span& span)
1960 {
1961     ClassTypeSymbol* classType = defaultConstructor->ClassType();
1962     try
1963     {
1964         bool nothrow = true;
1965         std::unique_ptr<BoundFunction> boundFunction(new BoundFunction(GetModule(), defaultConstructor));
1966         boundFunction->SetBody(     std::unique_ptr<BoundCompoundStatement>(new BoundCompoundStatement(GetModule(), span)));
1967         if (classType->StaticConstructor())
1968         {
1969             boundFunction->Body()->AddStatement(     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(new BoundExpressionStatement(GetModule(), std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundFunctionCall(GetModule(), span, 
1970                 classType->StaticConstructor())))));
1971             if (!classType->StaticConstructor()->DontThrow()) nothrow = false;
1972         }
1973         if (classType->BaseClass())
1974         {
1975             std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> baseConstructorCallLookups;
1976             baseConstructorCallLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
1977             baseConstructorCallLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_, classType->BaseClass()->GetContainerScope()));
1978             baseConstructorCallLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
1979             std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> baseConstructorCallArguments;
1980             ParameterSymbol* thisParam = defaultConstructor->Parameters()[0];
1981             ArgumentMatch argumentMatch;
1982             FunctionSymbol* thisToBaseConversion = GetBoundCompileUnit().GetConversion(thisParam->GetType(), classType->BaseClass()->AddPointer(span), containerScope, currentFunction, span, argumentMatch);
1983             if (!thisToBaseConversion)
1984             {
1985                 throw Exception(GetModule(), "base class conversion not found", span, classType->GetSpan());
1986             }
1987             BoundExpression* baseClassPointerConversion = new BoundConversion(GetModule(),      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundParameter(GetModule(), span, thisParam)), thisToBaseConversion);
1988             baseConstructorCallArguments.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(baseClassPointerConversion));
1989             std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> baseConstructorCall = ResolveOverload(U"@constructor", containerScope, baseConstructorCallLookups, baseConstructorCallArguments, GetBoundCompileUnit(), 
1990                 boundFunction.get(), span);
1991             if (!baseConstructorCall->GetFunctionSymbol()->DontThrow()) nothrow = false;
1992             boundFunction->Body()->AddStatement(     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(new BoundExpressionStatement(GetModule(), std::move(baseConstructorCall))));
1993         }
1994         if (classType->IsPolymorphic())
1995         {
1996             ParameterSymbol* thisParam = defaultConstructor->Parameters()[0];
1997             BoundExpression* classPtr = nullptr;
1998             ClassTypeSymbol* vmtPtrHolderClass = classType->VmtPtrHolderClass();
1999             if (vmtPtrHolderClass == classType)
2000             {
2001                 classPtr = new BoundParameter(GetModule(), span, thisParam);
2002             }
2003             else
2004             {
2005                 ArgumentMatch argumentMatch;
2006                 FunctionSymbol* thisToHolderConversion = GetBoundCompileUnit().GetConversion(thisParam->GetType(), vmtPtrHolderClass->AddPointer(span), containerScope, currentFunction, span, argumentMatch);
2007                 if (!thisToHolderConversion)
2008                 {
2009                     throw Exception(GetModule(), "base class conversion not found", span, classType->GetSpan());
2010                 }
2011                 classPtr = new BoundConversion(GetModule(),      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundParameter(GetModule(), span, thisParam)), thisToHolderConversion);
2012             }
2013             boundFunction->Body()->AddStatement(     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(new BoundSetVmtPtrStatement(GetModule(), std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(classPtr), classType)));
2014         }
2015         int n = classType->MemberVariables().size();
2016         for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i)
2017         {
2018             MemberVariableSymbol* memberVariableSymbol = classType->MemberVariables()[i];
2019             std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> memberConstructorCallLookups;
2020             memberConstructorCallLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
2021             memberConstructorCallLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_, memberVariableSymbol->GetType()->BaseType()->ClassInterfaceEnumDelegateOrNsScope()));
2022             memberConstructorCallLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
2023             std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> memberConstructorCallArguments;
2024             BoundMemberVariable* boundMemberVariable = new BoundMemberVariable(GetModule(), span, memberVariableSymbol);
2025             boundMemberVariable->SetClassPtr(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundParameter(GetModule(), span, defaultConstructor->GetThisParam())));
2026             memberConstructorCallArguments.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(
2027                 new BoundAddressOfExpression(GetModule(),      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(boundMemberVariable), boundMemberVariable->GetType()->AddPointer(span))));
2028             std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> memberConstructorCall = ResolveOverload(U"@constructor", containerScope, memberConstructorCallLookups, memberConstructorCallArguments, 
2029                 GetBoundCompileUnit(), boundFunction.get(), span);
2030             if (!memberConstructorCall->GetFunctionSymbol()->DontThrow()) nothrow = false;
2031             boundFunction->MoveTemporaryDestructorCallsTo(*memberConstructorCall);
2032             boundFunction->Body()->AddStatement(     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(new BoundExpressionStatement(GetModule(), std::move(memberConstructorCall))));
2033         }
2034         GetBoundCompileUnit().AddBoundNode(std::move(boundFunction));
2035         if (nothrow)
2036         {
2037             defaultConstructor->SetNothrow();
2038         }
2039     }
2040     catch (const Exception& ex;)
2041     {
2042         std::vector<Span> references;
2043         references.push_back(ex.Defined());
2044         references.insert(references.end(), ex.References().begin(), ex.References().end());
2045         exception.reset(new Exception(GetModule(), "cannot create default constructor for class '" + ToUtf8(classType->FullName()) + "'. Reason: " + ex.Message(), span, references));
2046         return false;
2047     }
2048     return  true;
2049 }

3518                 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> memberDestructorCallArguments;

3520                 boundMemberVariable->SetClassPtr(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundParameter(module, span, destructorSymbol->GetThisParam())));

3526             }
3527         }
3528         if (classType->BaseClass() && classType->BaseClass()->HasNontrivialDestructor())
3529         {
3530             std::vector<FunctionScopeLookup> baseDestructorCallLookups;
3531             baseDestructorCallLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_and_base_and_parent, containerScope));
3532             baseDestructorCallLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::this_, classType->BaseClass()->GetContainerScope()));
3533             baseDestructorCallLookups.push_back(FunctionScopeLookup(ScopeLookup::fileScopes, nullptr));
3534             std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>> baseDestructorCallArguments;
3535             ArgumentMatch argumentMatch;
3536             FunctionSymbol* thisToBaseConversion = boundCompileUnit.GetConversion(thisParam->GetType(), classType->BaseClass()->AddPointer(span), containerScope, boundFunction, 
3537                 span, argumentMatch);
3538             if (!thisToBaseConversion)
3539             {
3540                 throw Exception(module, "base class conversion not found", destructorNode->GetSpan(), classType->GetSpan());
3541             }
3542             BoundExpression* baseClassPointerConversion = new BoundConversion(module,      std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(new BoundParameter(module, span, thisParam)), thisToBaseConversion);
3543             baseDestructorCallArguments.push_back(     std::unique_ptr<BoundExpression>(baseClassPointerConversion));
3544             std::unique_ptr<BoundFunctionCall> baseDestructorCall = ResolveOverload(U"@destructor", containerScope, baseDestructorCallLookups, baseDestructorCallArguments, boundCompileUnit, 
3545                 boundFunction, span);
3546             boundCompoundStatement->AddStatement(     std::unique_ptr<BoundStatement>(new BoundExpressionStatement(module, std::move(baseDestructorCall))));
3547         }
3548     }
3549     catch (const Exception& ex;)
3550     {

3552         references.push_back(ex.Defined());
3553         references.insert(references.end(), ex.References().begin(), ex.References().end());

3555     }
